narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Further skills in speaking Czech, reading literature, and understanding the grammatical foundations of the language.

In class we continued to build off of Czech grammar that we had established in prior classes, and working into more challenging aspects of the grammar. We also spent a lot of time reading a novel to provide context of the grammar we were learning.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Got to cover a wide array of the parts of the Czech language! We got to read Kundera and create presentations, learning from context. I think a little more focus on learning vocabulary, or integrating the grammar lessons, would be helpful.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Czech is a fascinating language and culture!

I recommend this class to anyone interested in fulfilling their language credit in a less conventional way and in a low stress environment. My Czech classes have been my favorite classes I have take thus far at Yale. It is an interesting language, and an interesting culture to hear about. The class is very low-key and the prof is incredibly interested in making sure you genuinely understand the language and content of the class.
